Speaker 1: Or were you sticking with the generic?

Speaker 1: It don't work at all.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 2: If you wanted, you could put this on a pause, and then eventually when you did the penal injections,

Speaker 1: if you felt comfortable combining the two, that is always an option.

Speaker 2: So you could keep the prescription active and open in case you wanted to get refills of this later down the road.

Speaker 1: I don't.

Speaker 2: I don't.

Speaker 1: I appreciate you saying that, but if I do change my mind, I'll just contact you again.

Speaker 2: No, sir.

Speaker 2: I was kind of surprised because the credit card you had on file expired, but y'all somehow got my updated card.

Speaker 1: I don't know how that happened, but either way, I need that everything totaled.

Speaker 2: I don't want no more automatic refills.

Speaker 1: Peter?

Speaker 2: Yes, sir.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: I went ahead and closed it out.

Speaker 2: So, yeah, the current prescription is officially closed out.

Speaker 1: Thank you.

Speaker 2: Refills aren't even accessible under this account anymore, so you will not receive any more.

Speaker 1: Thank you, and if things get better, and I'd like to get back with you guys, I sure will give you a call,

Speaker 1: Of course.

Speaker 2: Of course.

Speaker 1: All right, Mr. Lancaster, that's all set.

Speaker 1: Nick.

Speaker 1: I did.

Speaker 2: I believe so.

Speaker 1: Mm-hmm.

Speaker 1: But you've got a great personality, Nick.
